OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCo-op warns of 'no-go'     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fareas as crime in shops    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsoars                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Co-op has warned some communities  
OL,6, could become "no-go" areas for shops   
OL,7, due to soaring levels of retail crime. 
OL,9,FThe convenience store operator said    
OL,10,Fcrime in its outlets had hit record    
OL,11,Flevels, increasing by more than one    
OL,12,Fthird over the past year.              
OL,14,FThere were about 1,000 cases of crime, 
OL,15,Fshoplifting and anti-social behaviour  
OL,16,Fin its shops every day in the six      
OL,17,Fmonths to June, the chain said.        
OL,19,FBut it cited figures indicating police 
OL,20,Fdid not attend most retail crimes.     
